# Environment Variables for Data Analytics Agent
# 
# This is a project-level .env.example file.
# For local development, create .env files in:
#   - apps/agent/.env (for backend)
#   - apps/web/.env.local (for frontend, if needed)
#
# See apps/agent/.env.example for detailed backend configuration

# ============================================
# BACKEND (.env in apps/agent/)
# ============================================

# Required:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
# DOMAIN=data_analytics

# Optional:
# MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# MAX_MESSAGE_HISTORY=100

# ============================================
# FRONTEND (.env.local in apps/web/)
# ============================================

# Optional - API URL (defaults to http://localhost:8123 in dev, /api in production)
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8123

# ============================================
# QUICK SETUP
# ============================================

# 1. Copy the example file:
#    cp apps/agent/.env.example apps/agent/.env

# 2. Edit apps/agent/.env and add your ANTHROPIC_API_KEY

# 3. Set DOMAIN=data_analytics for the analytics agent

# 4. Start the backend:
#    cd apps/agent
#    source .venv/bin/activate
#    python3 -m uvicorn src.pmm_agent.server:app --port 8123

# 5. Start the frontend (in another terminal):
#    cd apps/web
#    npm run dev
